My first attempt failed, that one is tested and works :)
How to create json:
public static Json writeTest(Json json, Test t){
        json.initialzeJsonWriter();
        json.writeObjectStart();
        json.writeObjectStart("tester");
        json.writeValue("className", t.getClass().getName(), String.class);
        json.writeValue("test", t, t.getClass());
        json.writeObjectEnd();
        json.writeObjectEnd();
        return json;
    }
How to get String:
writeTest(json, test).getString();
to prettyprint it:
json.prettyPrint(writeTest(json, test).getString(),0);

I think that's quite usefull if you don't have an object, but want to create a json.
best regards

